      "role": "user",
      "content": "but the UN resolution actually only authorized a no-fly zone to protect civilians, not to support the rebels. if the outcome was basically just making the country collapse for the sake of regime change, doesn't that make the \"R2P\" justification kind of a stretch in hindsight?",
